{"title":"milKit Hassle’Off Multitool Packs an Impressive Number of Tools Behind Your Bottle Cage","link":"https://bikerumor.com/milkit-hassleoff-multitool-under-bike-bottle-cage/","date":1680887324000,"content":"<p>Are you ready to party your Hasselhoff? No, not with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Hasselhoff\" target=\"_blank\">the guy</a> that holds the World Record for the “most-watched man on TV”. Nope, instead, It’ll be with the tool and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/milkit-tubeless-sealant-promises-longer-lasting-performance-good-for-up-to-6mm-cuts/\" target=\"_blank\">sealant company</a>, milKit’s new hassle-free<a href=\"https://milkit.bike/hassleoff/\" target=\"_blank\"> multitool</a> the Hassle’Off. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-on-tree-with-parts-out-e1680821851843.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"431\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-on-tree-with-parts-out-e1680821851843-800x431.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool on tree with parts out\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-on-tree-with-parts-out-e1680821851843-800x431.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-on-tree-with-parts-out-e1680821851843-297x160.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-on-tree-with-parts-out-e1680821851843-120x65.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-on-tree-with-parts-out-e1680821851843-768x414.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-on-tree-with-parts-out-e1680821851843.jpeg 1276w\" /></a><figcaption>Photo c. milKit </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Not unlike “The Hoff”, this new multi-tool could save you. Save you from being stuck with a technical issue while out riding. The tool boasts that even with its 20 functions, including a chain breaker, it’s lighter than your smartphone at 135g.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The tool looks pretty compact and can fit inside a pocket easily enough, but can also attach directly to the frame via water bottle bosses. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-8-bit-tool-on-rock-e1680822041587.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"461\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-8-bit-tool-on-rock-e1680822041587-800x461.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-8-bit-tool-on-rock-e1680822041587-800x461.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-8-bit-tool-on-rock-e1680822041587-297x171.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-8-bit-tool-on-rock-e1680822041587-120x69.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-8-bit-tool-on-rock-e1680822041587-768x443.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-8-bit-tool-on-rock-e1680822041587.jpeg 1260w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Hassle’Off uses what they are calling the Essential8 at the core of the tool. It is a magnet bit-in-bit that contains all of the common sizes to do most tightening and loosening on your steed, (hex, 8, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2.5, 2, and Torx25). The Essetial8 is constructed of stainless steel and is capable of high leverage, making the tool “workshop-quality that meets the highest quality standards”. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-plug-tool-e1680822320184.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"759\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-plug-tool-e1680822320184-800x759.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool tire plug tool\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-plug-tool-e1680822320184-800x759.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-plug-tool-e1680822320184-297x282.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-plug-tool-e1680822320184-120x114.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-plug-tool-e1680822320184-768x729.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-plug-tool-e1680822320184.jpeg 1024w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-Swiss-Army-Tool-cutter-e1680822294677.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"680\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-Swiss-Army-Tool-cutter-e1680822294677-800x680.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool Swiss Army Tool cutter\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-Swiss-Army-Tool-cutter-e1680822294677-800x680.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-Swiss-Army-Tool-cutter-e1680822294677-297x252.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-Swiss-Army-Tool-cutter-e1680822294677-120x102.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-Swiss-Army-Tool-cutter-e1680822294677-768x653.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-Swiss-Army-Tool-cutter-e1680822294677.jpeg 1024w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Hassle’Off sports an integrated tubeless plug solution for those times when sealant just isn’t going to cut it alone. The easily accessible Plug Tool has a side-loading shape that is supposed to make it easy to load. It has a twist shape that will “ensure the ideal positioning of the plug when it’s pushed into the tire.” </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The integrated, Swiss Army knife-style tool makes it easy to cut off the excess plug material, with storage for extra replacement plugs on the inside of the tool. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-spin-still-frame.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-spin-still-frame-800x300.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool spin still frame\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-spin-still-frame-800x300.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-spin-still-frame-297x111.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-spin-still-frame-120x45.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-spin-still-frame-768x288.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-spin-still-frame.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounting-under-water-bottle.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounting-under-water-bottle-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool mounting under water bottle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounting-under-water-bottle-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounting-under-water-bottle-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounting-under-water-bottle-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounting-under-water-bottle-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounting-under-water-bottle-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounting-under-water-bottle.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounted-under-water-bottle.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounted-under-water-bottle-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool mounted under water bottle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounted-under-water-bottle-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounted-under-water-bottle-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounted-under-water-bottle-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounted-under-water-bottle-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounted-under-water-bottle-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-mounted-under-water-bottle.jpg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But, the modularity of the tool with the integrated attachments for other equipment is really what makes this tool different. It allows for the tool to be customized to each rider’s personal needs. You can use the included Velcro strap to attach a tube, pump, or CO2 cartridge.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-water-bottle-side-e1680822626975.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"462\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-water-bottle-side-e1680822626975-800x462.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool water bottle side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-water-bottle-side-e1680822626975-800x462.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-water-bottle-side-e1680822626975-297x171.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-water-bottle-side-e1680822626975-120x69.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-water-bottle-side-e1680822626975-768x443.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-water-bottle-side-e1680822626975.jpeg 1142w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-pump-side-e1680822653865.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"470\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-pump-side-e1680822653865-800x470.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool pump side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-pump-side-e1680822653865-800x470.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-pump-side-e1680822653865-297x175.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-pump-side-e1680822653865-120x71.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-pump-side-e1680822653865-768x452.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-pump-side-e1680822653865.jpeg 1148w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-holding-pump-e1680822596828.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"557\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-holding-pump-e1680822596828-800x557.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool holding pump\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-holding-pump-e1680822596828-800x557.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-holding-pump-e1680822596828-297x207.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-holding-pump-e1680822596828-120x84.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-holding-pump-e1680822596828-768x535.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-holding-pump-e1680822596828.jpeg 1148w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>milKit created what they are calling a “holistic ecosystem” by providing a full range of tools that can be directly attached to the sliding interfaces of the Hassle’Off multitool. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-on-rock.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-on-rock-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool chain breaker on rock\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-on-rock-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-on-rock-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-on-rock-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-on-rock-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-on-rock-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-on-rock.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-lever-and-chain-breaker-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-lever-and-chain-breaker--800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool tire lever and chain breaker\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-lever-and-chain-breaker--800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-lever-and-chain-breaker--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-lever-and-chain-breaker--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-lever-and-chain-breaker--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-lever-and-chain-breaker--720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-tire-lever-and-chain-breaker-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-tire-lever-e1680822724657.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"636\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-tire-lever-e1680822724657-800x636.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool chain breaker tire lever\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-tire-lever-e1680822724657-800x636.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-tire-lever-e1680822724657-297x236.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-tire-lever-e1680822724657-120x95.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-tire-lever-e1680822724657-768x610.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-chain-breaker-tire-lever-e1680822724657.jpeg 1014w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To save space the chain breaker blends seamlessly with the tire lever and is magnetically compatible with the Essential8. The chain breaker itself is a spoke wrench and valve core tool, again saving space within the tool. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Hassle’Off is made of glass-fiber reinforced “high-performance” material as well as the aforementioned stainless steel. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-with-velcro-on-tree-e1680822824404.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"329\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-with-velcro-on-tree-e1680822824404-800x329.jpeg\" alt=\"milKit Hassle'Off tool with velcro on tree\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-with-velcro-on-tree-e1680822824404-800x329.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-with-velcro-on-tree-e1680822824404-297x122.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-with-velcro-on-tree-e1680822824404-120x49.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-with-velcro-on-tree-e1680822824404-768x316.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/milKit-HassleOff-tool-with-velcro-on-tree-e1680822824404.jpeg 1273w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This inventive lil’ tool is available now and retails for $99.95. Hit the link below to get yours. </p>\n\n\n\n<p> <em><a href=\"https://milkit.bike/\" target=\"_blank\">MilKit.Bike</a></em></p>\n\n\n\n<p> </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/milkit-hassleoff-multitool-under-bike-bottle-cage/\">milKit Hassle’Off Multitool Packs an Impressive Number of Tools Behind Your Bottle Cage</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d89b5bb8b32418755fd71010dc8b34df54029a045adaa762bf72e1e22c9d2c6e","category":"Cycling"}